[SN]TITLE[SN]
Stolen car crashed into police vehicle in Caol

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Police have sought the driver of a stolen car that collided with a police vehicle in Caol near Fort William.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The driver and a passenger of the Audi A4 got out and fled the scene in the incident, which happened at about 22:15 on Sunday in Glen Nevis Road.
The stolen car caught fire and firefighters were called and extinguished the flames.
Police Scotland said the passenger had been detained and was assisting police with inquiries.
Ch Insp Bob Mackay said: "I would urge the driver of the Audi to come forward to confirm they are safe and well."
